A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Atlanta Jewish Film Festival on its 25th anniversary; and for other
2 purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Atlanta Jewish Film Festival (AJFF) is the largest film festival in Atlanta
4 and the State of Georgia as well as one of the largest Jewish film festivals in the world; and
5 WHEREAS, the AJFF inspires communities to new levels of social and cultural
6 understanding by entertaining and engaging diverse audiences with film observed through
7 a Jewish lens; and
8 WHEREAS, AJFF cooperates with leaders from various religious, ethnic, cultural, and
9 educational groups, including public and private schools, colleges and universities, to create
10 programming that deepens dialogue and bonds between communities; and
11 WHEREAS, AJFF works in partnership with its founder, the Atlanta Regional Office of
12 American Jewish Committee (AJC), a global advocacy organization that enhances the
13 well-being of the Jewish people and Israel through education, outreach, and diplomacy; and
