14 WHEREAS, the annual festival was founded in 2000 by the AJC, and its inaugural group of
15 filmgoers amounted to more than 1,900; by 2006, that figure had increased to about 7,500,
16 and by 2008, they began adjusting their itinerary to include more dates and bigger venues to
17 hold nearly 15,000 filmgoers; and
18 WHEREAS, for their tenth anniversary, AJFF had a concert of iconic Jewish film scores,
19 presented in partnership with the Atlanta Symphony Orchestra and Turner Classic Movies,
20 resulting in nearly 20,000 moviegoers; and
21 WHEREAS, in 2015, the AJFF made history by becoming the largest Jewish film festival
22 in the world, attracting more than 38,600 moviegoers; and
23 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable festival be appropriately
24 honored during this special time.
25 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE that the members of this body
26 commend the Atlanta Jewish Film Festival upon its 25th anniversary for its many
27 contributions to the arts in our community and for fostering stronger ties by educating
28 communities that have religious, ethnic, and cultural differences.
29 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Secretary of the Senate is authorized and directed
30 to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to the Atlanta Jewish
31 Film Festival.
